main event: A reported sighting of a flying object emitting irregular flashing lights passing from west to east at high altitude on June 16, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed by military personnel on the USS Tete-a-tete., The object did not appear to be on a straight course., The sighting was made via ground radar., The reported position of the object was 39.5°N 152.6°E., The object was noted to be very high and exhibited irregular light patterns.
sighted object: flying object emitting irregular flashing lights
